			I took care of the blog and the many photos. Steffi checked finances and took care of our provisions. Then we simply decided to jump into the pool and enjoy the sun for the rest of the day. In the evening we decided that we are going to Green Island today. </p>
		<p> So this morning we made our way back to the harbor. When we arrived at the ship, we were very quickly surrounded by Asians. The captain then greeted us with the words "Welcome to China". Well, we just thought and unfortunately that should be confirmed. </p>
		<p> About 1000 Chinese frolicked on the only 600m long island. Far too much for this beautiful little oasis. First we registered for a boat dive and spontaneously decided to take Steffi out for snorkeling. That was the right decision, because when we came to the beach a few minutes later we found that ebb was and therefore the water is too flat to snorkel from the beach. </p>
		<p> We would then rather decide to eat a little something before finally going out the 700m to the diving site by boat. 
			It was a very flat dive with a maximum depth of only 3.6m but that was more than okay. </p>
